sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1475010
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: dxs+LIMS1+appY regulated by the tet promoter
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part is the limonene generator with tet promoter. The limonene generator consists of deoxyxylulose phosphtae synthase (dxs), limonene synthase (LIMS1) and appY.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Daniel Weltz Pedersen

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K118024
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: ''dxs'', from ''Escherichia coli'' JM109, encodes 1-deoxyxylulose-5-phosphate synthase, thiamine-requiring, which catalyses the first step in the biosynthesis of terpenoids. Overexpression of ''dxs'' has been reported to increase yields of carotenoids and other terpenoids [add reference here]. ''lims1'', from ''Citrus limon'', encodes limonene synthase, which produces (+)-limonene from farnesyl diphosphate (an intermediate in the mevalonate pathway). (+)-Limonene is a component of lemon scent. ''appY'', from ''Escherichia coli'' JM109, encodes a transcriptional regulator related to anaerobic energy metabolism. Overexpression of the gene has been reported to result in enhanced lycopene production by ''E. coli'' (Kang ''et al.'', 2005). (All three genes are individually preceded by a ribosome binding site.)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Andrew Hall
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: ''dxs'' and ''appY'' are both from ''E. coli'' JM109 genomic DNA. ''lims1'' is from ''Citrus limon'' genomic DNA.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: The order of the genes in the operon corresponds to our perceived importance of each gene, bearing in mind that translation is more efficient of the genes early in the mRNA.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_J15001
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: strong synthetic E. coli ribosome binding site with SacI site.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is a strong synthetic E. coli ribosome binding site. It is synthesised as two complementary oligonucleotides rather than being incorporated into a biobrick plasmid. It incorporates a SacI site overlapping the XbaI site, which is preserved when it is added to any other biobrick. This allows easy detection of the RBS after it has been added upstream of a biobrick coding sequence in a plasmid vector.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Chris French
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Note the presence of a SacI site overlapping the XbaI site, which is preserved when this biobrick is added to any other biobrick. At the time of writing, this biobrick is added as a short piece of DNA composed of two complementary oligonucleotides rather than being incorporated into a biobrick cloning vector by itself. It can be added upstream of a biobrick coding sequence, and its presence can easily be detected in miniprep DNA on a gel by using a SacI-SpeI or similar digest.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: LIMS1
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
Limonene synthase 1 from Citrus limon (accession AF514287) Synthesised by Geneart.
Limonene synthase converts farnesyl-diphosphate to + limonene, which is a component of lemon scent.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: sarah hollingshead
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance:
Monoterpene biosynthesis in lemon (Citrus limon) cDNA isolation and functional analysis of four monoterpene synthases, J Lucker, et al, Eur. J. Biochem. 269: 3160???3171 (2002)
Analysis of Lemon and Bergamot Essential Oils by HPLC with Microbore Columns, M Benincasa, et al, Chromatographia 30(5/6):271 (1990)
Citrus fruit flavour and aroma biosynthesis, L Sharon-Asa, The Plant Journal, 36:664 (2003)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: several codons were altered silently to remove several forbidden restriction sites. The N-terminal region (plastid targeting sequence) was removed, removing the first 51 amino acids and replacing codon 52 with the start codon ATG

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0012
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcription terminator for the E.coli RNA polymerase.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Derived from the TE terminator of T7 bacteriophage between Genes 1.3 and 1.4 <genbank>V01146</genbank>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Suggested by Sri Kosuri and Drew Endy as a high efficiency terminator. The 5' end cutoff was placed immediately after the TAA stop codon and the 3' end cutoff was placed just prior to the RBS of Gene 1.4 (before AAGGAG).

Use anywhere transcription should be stopped when the gene of interest is upstream of this terminator.
